<br>
I think that anyone can be good, or anyone can be evil. It all comes down to the person. Some races have strong tendencies towards one extreme or the other. That is eood and high elves towards being goodly aligned and so on.  Now can there be an evil wood elf'? Sure, why not. Will this evil wood elf live long? not likely in my opinion. It seems to be that such a one would either get found out and killed by his fellows or would leave for another city before getting caught.<br>
<br>
Now here is where it gets interesting... think abuot Drizzt in EQ terms... he would be &quot;KoS&quot; in almost any city after leaving Menzo, and still probably is in many even after becoming &quot;uber&quot; and well known. <br>
<br>
I think that if someone was to be the evil wood elf, or the good dark elf, they would have to spend all that time re-adjusting their faction so that they were at least tolerated (even if suspiciously) to be taken seriously RP wise... showing everyone else of the alignment, that they are willing to put the time into it, to play this type of character<br>
<br>
Now as for guild will they be welcome in an all evil guild or an all good one? Id like to think no. Here is my reason. While they may have  become accpeted in many of the darker cities and whatnot they will certainly never be welcomed there. Not enough Trust (does even exist between the evils ;P ) dont know if that is the right word but I think yall can see what I mean. I think that by trying to play one of these characters you are accepting the life of an outcast and a loner... IC at least never to truely be welcomed anywhere.<br>
<br>
Just some random rambling during some downtime *grin*<br>
<br>
