<br>
Certainly if I ran around saying I'm a gnome without doing gnomish things or gaining Ak'Anon faction, I wouldn't expect to have a hope of having my RP taken seriously until I could freely salute King Ak'Anon.  And likewise if I wanted to be the new Drizzt and run around saying I'm good, I wouldn't even bother saying so till I was able to walk freely in Queynos, Freeport, Kelethin and Felwithe at least.  <br>
<br>
So yeah ... in fact I do choose to call myself a defender of Ak'Anon, and I believe it would mean nothing if I wasn't really able to walk freely around the gnomish NPCs as well as players.  I believe roleplay isn't entirely in your mind, and that you should put in the faction work to allow you to live up to your claims.  Put thy (f)actions where thy mouth is, or don't expect to be anything but laughed at, is my personal opinion.<br>
